Let's enhance the configuration file (git-aliases) with helpful GitHub-related shortcuts. These shortcuts will cover common tasks such as opening the repository page, creating a pull request, and listing issuesâ€”all in shorthand format.
Complete git-aliases File with Useful Shortcuts

Here's a sample git-aliases configuration that includes the following:

    openrepo: Opens the GitHub repository in the default browser.
    pr: Creates a pull request for the current branch.
    prlist: Lists all open pull requests.
    issues: Lists all open issues.
    checkoutpr: Checks out a pull request by number.

ini

# git-aliases: Enhanced Git and GitHub CLI Shortcuts

[alias]
    # Basic Commands
    st = status                    # Show working directory status
    cm = commit -m                 # Commit with a message
    co = checkout                  # Checkout a branch
    br = branch                    # List branches
    lg = log --oneline --graph --all --decorate  # Pretty git log

    # Advanced Commands
    amend = commit --amend --no-edit  # Amend the last commit without changing the message
    rb = rebase                       # Start a rebase
    stashp = stash pop                # Apply stashed changes and remove from stash
    chp = cherry-pick                 # Apply a commit from another branch
    bis = bisect                      # Start a bisect to find a bug

    # GitHub Shortcuts
    openrepo = "!f() { url=$(git config --get remote.origin.url | sed -e 's/git@github.com:/https:\\/\\/github.com\\//' -e 's/.git$//'); if [ -z \"$url\" ]; then echo 'No remote repository found.'; else case \"$OSTYPE\" in darwin*) open \"$url\" ;; linux*) xdg-open \"$url\" ;; msys*) start \"$url\" ;; *) echo 'Unsupported OS' ;; esac; fi; }; f"
    